It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house that hasn't been touched except for a little decorating.
The awful electric fireplace and the fireplace hearth have to go. We need to build a wall around the fireplace, replace the chipped plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom-made wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dried up :(
Everything is ready for the stucco artist next week
The small side niche has turned out well
Here comes a new wardrobe (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought about incorporating this nice little vent flap, so that the fireplace doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and cap. Now it should be a little safer for the crows that like to nest up there 🪺
The stucco artist is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlayment is in place, I made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be laid. We are having tea break right now
Buhu. Progress is slow today due to super complicated cuts around the door posts so we can have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be laid anew). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Done, but at the end! The crowning moment was the terrible installation instructions for the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator is coming in a month, so we currently have the rough plaster look.
Some more DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel out the lower sections around the door posts, so the floor can fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayment is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then we left at 5 a.m. to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, had a little nap, and then a final push in the hallway, the baseboards are installed. The joints will be done once the glue is dry.
